arch:property.oc:show_val: Medium-large unit coming from an arbitrary layer within the midden in the space 86. Mostly sheep-size, few large mammal bones. Large mammal is mostly cranial. Fragments of ?Bos cranium. Fragments of horn cores, but not a lot. 20 % burnt (carbonized and calcined). Various weathering. ID: sheep cranial and postcranial, few bird, micromammals and cattle remains. At least 4 juvenile and one adult Ovis/Capra. One of them identified as Ovis on the base of right and left branch of mandible probably from a single animal. Broken in many pieces (recent breaks), but a fragment of a left branch shows old break. Possibly broken when thrown into the midden. X4 Bos primigenius mandibula. Jaw bone could not be reconstructed and is packed in a bag with an explanatory label, while three molars are reconstructed. Both sheep/goat and cattle phalanges are highly fragmented, although not gnawed or digested. Bone grease? Looks like midden, with more deterioration than most due to proximity to ground surface. Samples 1 and 3 >4 mm flotation 100% sorted; only diagnostics recorded, rest as flot frags. Sample 1 is largish and looks generally like the unit as a whole, with a variety of taxa and body parts, although little if any horn core. Some microfauna, eggshell, mussel shell, and a burnt small bird tarsometatarsus. Rather fragmented and worn, but some larger chunks. Sample 3 is smaller and has less large mammal. Last number = 345

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
